rComments: honestly a really good prof. always replies to his emails and is also really funny (according to me) do your part, ask questions and you should be fine. don't be scared to book apt with him.

Great professor! Teaching methods are engaging and effective. The only thing I would change is his organizational skills-the syllabus was unclear, and didn't match other parts of the course schedule outline. I bought the course pack, but just skim/scan, average 40pages to read a week. Go to class for notes 2write the projects/online midterm&final:)

Mr. Boulou is charming in the beginning of his class, but you come to realize that he isn't. He becomes very comfortable with the class, his opinion becomes the only one that matters, if you express question/concerns or a different opinion he practically will shame you in front of the class. He goes on rants and makes up words. He yells and is mean

Boulou is a great guy with a great sense of humour, but his expectations for the entry course into cinema are high as hell. I took it as an elective and a lot of it was interesting, but it was hard. He literally said that "to do well in this class, you need to study fifteen hours a week." Who has time for that? If you do, take this course.

He is a nice person and his classes are fun most of the time. However, he has a lot of trouble communicating ideas and concepts to students in an effective manner. Moreover, his tests are very unfair as they do not reflect course material. Instead of focusing on the main topics covered in class,  they focus on insignificant facts from the textbook.

He is so fun! He engages all the students during the lecture and uses lots of examples to illustrate. He does like to call on people for answers, but he moves on to another person if you dont have the answer. My fave prof so far, lots of fun and very easy to listen to.
He is rash and makes claims that are unfounded.  He attempts to intimidate - and it works on some.  Be careful, this guy has something to prove.
He is a very passionate teacher that cares very much for his students. He can open up your mind and make you think in a way you never imagined.

i agree with what everyone has says. he calls on his students to answer questions, and won't stop asking until you get it right. don't bother going to class if you haven't read the text...he'll kick you out. his midterms were unfair and is impossible to argue with, since 'he's always right'.

I HATE THIS MAN! For our take-home midterm he "caught" 20 people for plaigarism. They were crying in his office defending himself while he was yelling at them. Many of the students also had rough work to prove that they did not copy other students. He's VERY arrogant. Never replies to emails. Often scolds those who email him. STAY AWAY FROM HIM!

Absolutely terrible prof. Blames his own inability to communicate on the students. One of the worst, most frustrating classes I ever took. Extremely arrogant and pompous without the skills to back it up.

This class was not fun to take by any means. There were often nasty comments on the discussion board between the prof and his students as he was unable to communicate properly with his students.He'll tell you to email him about a question and then never reply.He also shouts a lot during class and makes you do surprise presentations.NOT recommended.
very knowledgeable , very loud make sure you read your text beforehand , likes to ask random people questions.Loves class interaction

This prof is the worse.  He was always trying to be cool and smooth, while barely teaching anything.  I learned nothing in this class, and I hated every minute of it.  This prof also instituted mandatory group work, which I despise.

Worst prof ever. Makes absolutely no sense and tests on things that have barely been covered, most definitely not in depth. I will never take a course with him again. As far as I am concerned he should not be teaching at a University

Horrible Just Horrible.  I despise this prof...he said he was ashamed of some of his students because we didn't perform up to his high arrogant PhD standards.  Harsh, very harsh, disrespectful, likes to humiliate students in front of the class and shouts literally shouts when he talks.  He really needs to learn some ethical teaching methods. AVOID!
One of the worst teacher I had ... Remember... DO NOT TAKE CLASSES WITH BOULOU.. You'll suffer.
Total ****.  His knowledge of film is peripheral and he treats his students like garbage. Speaks awful.  Classes are dull.

Seems like a nice guy, but his class was pathetic. Not only could I not understand most of what he was saying because he was shouting too much, his tests were bogus and the questions were completely random. He turned me off from communications.

He may be a nice man, but he's a horrible professor! His lecture notes do not have anything to do with the tests, and the final exam was EXTREMELY unfair. I don't recommend him at all! If you have him as a prof, memorize the textbook - he will pick the most random questions. He gives pop-quizes and his movies are on the final. Unfair!!

This professor is a nut! He changed the course outline on us, he was extremely disorganized, surprised us with an extra presentation part way through the term. I will never, NEVER take another course with him again.
So far the best of my University profs.
No Comments

Doesn't follow his own deadlines, disapears for and misses classes without any real prior notice and comes late to class almost every day.  He's very unclear, his notes make no sense and when asked for clarification instead of answering himself he'll have other students answer you without saying whether or no they are really accurate.

I'm sure he's a very nice man, but I find his lectures and his teaching methods to be inaccessible. It may be the language barrier, or it may be that he tries to turn communications into a philosophy course.

Very nice guy but, even though I am not stupid, I just cannot follow what he is teaching. He has doctorate in philo so that might be why. I love the person, but I hate his lecturing. I find his topics lack transition and he is scattered. Slides = useless.

While he's very nice and very funny - and probably quite smart, he is difficult to understand. The first class he spoke slowly enough, but after that it was like listening to a different language. and he runs through his slides too quickly.
The best of the best. Funny, hut, teaching with class.
Probably a very nice person outside of class, but not very good as a teacher. Too much work--please realise that we have other courses! Group essay too, which is ridiculous at this level.
he's just the best i've seen so far
the best prof i want to be. he's good
